itunes:summary:
Ross Patterson and Dan Hollaway welcome special guest, former Navy Seal Ephraim Mattos to discuss Stronghold Rescue and Relief, which is one of the most insane non-profit groups on the planet.  His missions to Burma and Venezuela are not only inspiring, but he is put into the worst possible conditions every with his life on the line every single day.  He tells us why he does it, the craziest missions he's been on, and what it REALLY takes to be a Navy Seal.  Powerful show.
